  "text": "For example, [CITATION_1] , and [CITATION_2] stress the role of participation constraints to generate inefficiency. However, international environmental agreements are generally preceded by discussion rounds during which concerned parties do not negotiate pollution abatement targets but can communicate with each other and exchange information. This paper takes a mechanism design approach and studies the effect of asymmetric information about pollution abatement costs on the feasibility of an efficient environmental agreement when participation to this agreement is voluntary and when countries can communicate before negotiations start.",
